org.knime.core.node.dialog

Class ExternalNodeData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.dialog.ExternalNodeData

  • public class ExternalNodeData
extends Object
    This object represents output or input of a node for provided or consumed outside the workflow, e.g. in web service calls. The data can either be "small" amounts of data as in in-memory JSON object or larger amounts of data as file-based resources. Additional formats may be added over time. Objects are built using the ExternalNodeData.ExternalNodeDataBuilder which can be acquired via builder(String).
    Since:
    2.12
    Author:
    Thorsten Meinl, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

      • getID

        public String getID()
        Returns an ID for this data object (may be an empty string if the node is not configured yet).
        Returns:
        unique ID for the data object, never null

      • getJSONValue

        public javax.json.JsonValue getJSONValue()
        Returns node data as a generic JSON value. This should only be used for small data as it is kept in memory. The method may return null if no JSON data is provided.
        Data needs only be provided if the node/workflow is executed, but providing a template in case the node is configured is beneficial. If NO_JSON_VALUE_YET is returned this means that eventually JSON can be provided. A null value means that JSON may never be available.
        Returns:
        a JSON value, may be null

      • getStringValue

        public String getStringValue()
        Returns node data as a plain string. This should only be used for small data as it is kept in memory. The method may return null if no string data is provided.
        Data needs only be provided if the node/workflow is executed, but providing a template in case the node is configured is beneficial. If NO_STRING_VALUE_YET is returned this means that eventually JSON can be provided. A null value means that JSON may never be available.
        Returns:
        a string, may be null

      • getResource

        public URL getResource()
        Returns the URL to a larger resource. The URL is usually a file URL sitting in a temporary directory. The method may return null if no external resource is provided.
        Data needs only be provided if the node/workflow is executed, but providing a template in case the node is configured is beneficial. If NO_URL_VALUE_YET is returned this means that eventually JSON can be provided. A null value means that JSON may never be available.
        Returns:
        a URL to a resource, or null
